<%= section "Add a concept tag to an exercise" do %>

<p>Adding a concept tag to an exercise requires two separate processes: (1) create the concept tag and (2) link the concept tag to an exercise. The below tutorial describes both processes.</p>
<ol>
  <li><em>Create the concept tag</em> by navigating to the Concepts section of the Learning Plan;</li>
  <center>
		<%= image_tag("concept1.png", {:border => 1, :width => "80%", :height => "70%", :title=>"create new concept"})%>
	</center>
  <li>Click on New Concept;</li>
  <center>
		<%= image_tag("concept2.png", {:border => 1, :width => "80%", :height => "70%", :title=>"create new concept"})%>
	</center>
  <li>Type the concept name in the text box and click Create Concept to save;</li>
  <li>Return to the Topics section of the Learning Plan and open the topic where you will add the concept tag;</li>
  <li>Open the exercise requiring a concept tag (may be you need to add a new exercise, or edit an existing exercise) </li>
  <li><em>Add the concept tag to the exercise</em> by clicking on Choose a Concept and selecting the relevant topic;</li>
  <br/>
  <center>
		<%= image_tag("concept3.png", {:border => 1, :width => "80%", :height => "80%", :title=>"create new concept"})%>
	</center>
  <br/>
  <li>Click Update Topic exercise to save. Your concept should now appear next to your exercise.</li>
  <br/>
  <center>
		<%= image_tag("concept4.png", {:border => 1, :width => "80%", :height => "80%", :title=>"create new concept"})%>
	</center>
  <br/>
</ol>
<% end %>

